root_causes: The clause intended to flag non-EU respondents uses miss(flt) but flt is always set to 0 or 1, so miss(flt) will never be true. As a result, non-EU respondents with SI2 filled will not be flagged as required.
Because flt is initialized to 0, the miss(flt) branch is logically impossible â€” the script never checks flt = 0 to detect unexpected SI2 entries for non-EU respondents.
instructions: Replace the miss(flt) check with an explicit flt = 0 condition so non-EU respondents with SI2 populated are flagged. For example: sel if (flt = 1 and (miss(SI2) or SI2 = 2)) or (flt = 0 and ~miss(SI2)).

Optionally make the special-code allowance explicit (to ensure 97/98/99 are treated as non-flagging): change the EU missing check to exclude those codes, e.g. (flt = 1 and ((miss(SI2) and not SI2 in (97,98,99)) or SI2 = 2)).
Confirm that the list of qCountry codes used to set flt accurately reflects the project's isEU() definition (add/remove country codes as required).

root_causes: Missing entry condition restricting checks to non-screener respondents (f('qSurveyType').none('2'))
instructions: Apply the entry condition so validation and other-specify checks run only for respondents who meet the entry rule. For example, change the validation selection to: sel if qSurveyType <> 2 and ( miss(qCountry) or ~any(qCountry,1033,12,7,2057,10,16,3081,98) ).

Also restrict the Other-specify consistency check to the same respondents: sel if qSurveyType <> 2 and ((qCountry = 98 and (qCountry_98_other = "" or qCountry_98_other = ' ')) or (qCountry <> 98 and qCountry_98_other <> "" and qCountry_98_other <> ' ')).

root_causes: Missing entry condition restricting checks to non-screener respondents (f('qSurveyType').none('2'))
instructions: Restrict validation and hard-screen listing to respondents who satisfy the entry condition. For example, change validation to: sel if qSurveyType <> 2 and ( miss(SI1) or ~range(SI1,1,2) ).
Restrict the hard-screen listing similarly: sel if qSurveyType <> 2 and SI1 = 2.
